@Auco @Tuan Dao your models will not be exposed to any parties other than BitMind -- we'll continue to use the models to power our applications (mobile app dropping this week!!) as well as future b2b API usage that will drive revenue back to the subnet. yup! once you have your onnx file ready you can just run
```
gascli miner push --onnx-dir models/ --wallet-name <> --wallet-hotkey <>
```

Correct -- when your model gets executed it will be passed a tensor with values in [0, 255] and with arbitrary batch, frame, heigh and width dimensions. It is the job of the preprocessor that you wrap your model in to ensure that the data are scaled/shaped the right way for your model. Goal with that being to not be over-prescriptive about what you should and shouldn't do with the data 🙂

The only potentially tricky part here is making sure your wrapper is properly set up before creating your ONNX file -- the rest should be smooth.

# Release 4.0.0 - GAS ⛽ 
@mind・34  
Hi everyone -- T minus 1.5 hours to GAS mainnet! 

Testnet 379 will be down temporarily as we prepare for the migration.

1. Remove SN34 V3 repository and validator state.

2. Clone the repository and run the installation script.
```
$ git clone git@github.com:BitMind-AI/bitmind-subnet.git
$ cd bitmind-subnet/ && ./install.sh
```
The installation script provides quickstart instructions.

# Release 4.0.4 -- Model Entrance Exam + Local Benchmarking

We've added a model "entrance exam" that runs automatically on every new model submission. The entrance exam, which acts as a gatekeeper for more in-depth model evaluation, tests each submitted against the latest BitMind image/video benchmarks generated by the subnet. Benchmark outputs include:
- ONNX model validation (input/output shape and dtype checks)
- pass/fail result (currently set to 80% minimum accuracy)
- metrics so miners know where they stand
- verbose output options that show what the data sources for each sample to help you drill down on your model's potential weak points

You can also now reproduce the exact entrance exam locally with gascli!
Run image benchmark: `gascli miner benchmark --image-model /path/image.onnx`
Run video benchmark: `gascli miner benchmark --video-model /path/video.onnx`

Useful options:
```
-v | -vv | -vvv: increase logging
--stream-images: stream images instead of downloading
--prune-old-data: remove older cached splits/configs after fetching the latest
```

It’s decentralized AI, right? If you only give rewards to the single best model, it risks centralization instead of decentralization. A winner-take-all system means most miners won’t have any incentive to participate, which can shrink the diversity of models. Decentralization works best when many contributors are motivated to compete and collaborate — if you cut everyone out except one winner, you may lose robustness, innovation, and resilience. Reward distribution, even if skewed towards better performers, helps maintain a healthy ecosystem where different approaches can flourish, not just one dominant model.
